<section class="mb-10">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 pb-2 border-b-2 border-gray-200">The Challenge</h2>
<p class="mb-4">A financial services company ran a dual-system operation: an external platform tracked all client work and generated billing data, while NetSuite handled accounting. Invoices had to be manually recreated in NetSuite -- 200-300 per month, each taking 30-60 minutes of data entry.</p>

<div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-5 text-center shadow-sm border-t-4 border-accent">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary">150 hrs</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-1">Monthly Manual Entry</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-5 text-center shadow-sm border-t-4 border-accent">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary">25%</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-1">Invoice Error Rate</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-5 text-center shadow-sm border-t-4 border-accent">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary">5-7 days</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-1">Processing Delay</div>
    </div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="mb-10">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 pb-2 border-b-2 border-gray-200">The Solution: Multi-Stage Processing Pipeline</h2>

<div class="bg-gray-900 text-blue-300 p-5 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre my-4">Stage 1: Data Reception (RESTlet)
External System --POST--> NetSuite RESTlet
- Validate JSON structure
- Create tracking record (unique ID)
- Segment large invoices (100 lines each)
- Return confirmation (<2 seconds)
          |
          v
Stage 2: Automated Validation (User Event)
- Trigger on tracking record creation
- Validate customer references exist
- Parse complex line item structures
- Mark as "Ready for Processing"
          |
          v
Stage 3: Batch Invoice Creation (Map/Reduce)
- Runs every 15 minutes
- Parallel processing of validated invoices
- Intelligent line item consolidation:
    - By Service Line
    - By Resource Pool
    - By Item
    - No consolidation (full detail)
- Links created invoices to tracking records
          |
          v
Stage 4: Automated Delivery (Workflow)
- Generate branded PDF invoice
- Collect recipients from customer + invoice
- Send email with PDF attachment
- Record in communication history</div>

<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-light mt-6 mb-3">Intelligent Failure Handling</h3>
<div class="bg-gray-900 text-blue-300 p-5 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre my-4">Status-Driven State Machine:

Needs Parsing --> Pending --> Processed
      |              |
      v              v
    Error <---------+
      |
(Admin resets status to retry)</div>

<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-light mt-6 mb-3">Key Engineering Patterns</h3>
<table class="w-full text-sm my-4">
    <thead>
        <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="p-3 text-left font-semibold text-primary-light border-b-2 border-gray-200">Challenge</th>
            <th class="p-3 text-left font-semibold text-primary-light border-b-2 border-gray-200">Solution</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-3">Invoices with 500+ line items hit field size limits</td>
            <td class="p-3">Automatic segmentation into 100-line chunks with parallel processing and reassembly</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-3">Processing 300 invoices would timeout in single script</td>
            <td class="p-3">Multi-stage pipeline with independent governance budgets per stage</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-3">External system occasionally retries requests (duplicates)</td>
            <td class="p-3">Unique ID tracking with duplicate detection before processing</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-3">Some invoices fail while others succeed</td>
            <td class="p-3">Status-driven state machine with independent processing and retry</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-3">Different consolidation rules for different invoice types</td>
            <td class="p-3">Configuration field on invoice controls consolidation logic dynamically</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
